rblog.com/wordpress-theme-revolitioncars-adsenseready-3-columns-free-for-download/\">RevolutionCars</a> is a dark, 3-column theme with Adsense readiness.</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Thu, 22 Nov 2007 04:45:04 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:11:\"Jim Stitzel\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:492:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.blogohblog.com/wordpress-theme-atlantia/\">Atlantia</a> is a 2-column theme with striped background and sea-worthy header.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.askgraphics.com/freetemplates/divclear-wordpress-theme/\">DivClear</a> is a 2-column, light theme with third column for advertising.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.adivorblog.com/wordpress-theme-revolitioncars-adsenseready-3-columns-free-for-download/\">RevolutionCars</a> is a dark, 3-column theme with Adsense readiness.</p>\";}i:45;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"Donncha: A Simply Silly WordPress URL\";s:4:\"guid\";s:58:\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2007/11/21/a-simply-silly-wordpress-url/\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2007/11/21/a-simply-silly-wordpress-url/\";s:11:\"description\";s:2221:\"<p>I&#8217;m not sure why I noticed this protest sticker. It&#8217;s stuck to a lamp post on Patrick Street, Cork but maybe it was the typo in the URL that triggered my subconscious. One thing I can be certain of is that WordPress.org is not taking sides in any conflict of any sort! GPL software can be used by anyone just so long as they stick to the agreement with which they accepted the software.</p>\n<div align=\"center\"><img src=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-content/uploads/2007/11/sillystupidtypo.jpg\" alt=\"Silly Stupid Typo\" /></div>\n<p>As expected, <a href=\"http://palestinesolidarityproject.wordpress.com/\">palestinesolidarityproject.wordpress.com</a> points at an old blog of theirs as they have now moved to their own server at <a href=\"http://palestinesolidarityproject.org/\">palestinesolidarityproject.org</a>.</p>\n<p>Glossing over the .org mistake for a minute, why do people still put the &#8220;www.&#8221; in front of long-winded urls? It gets stripped by WordPress.com anyway. Why not put &#8220;http://&#8221; there instead? Makes more sense to me. Three cheers for the <a href=\"http://no-www.org/\">no-www</a> movement!</p>\n<p>So, have you seen any glaring typos on posters, fliers, stickers or blogs that made you look twice? Today&#8217;s <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2007/11/21/donnchas-thursday-links-2007-11-21/\">link post</a> doesn&#8217;t count. I did that on purpose to make a point. Sure. <img src=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/?voyeur=1\" /></p><p><strong>Related Posts</strong><ul><li><a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2004/01/26/vodafoneie-doesnt-like-mozilla-firebird/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Vodafone.ie doesn&#8217;t like Mozilla Firebird\">Vodafone.ie doesn&#8217;t like Mozilla Firebird</a></li><li><a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2005/08/17/whats-this-wordpresscom-thing-anyway/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: What&#8217;s this WordPress.com thing anyway?\">What&#8217;s this WordPress.com thing anyway?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2007/12/09/put-wordpress-on-the-map/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Put WordPress on the map\">Put WordPress on the map</a></li></ul></p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 21 Nov 2007 12:59:23 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:7:\"Donncha\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:2221:\"<p>I&#8217;m not sure why I noticed this protest sticker. It&#8217;s stuck to a lamp post on Patrick Street, Cork but maybe it was the typo in the URL that triggered my subconscious. One thing I can be certain of is that WordPress.org is not taking sides in any conflict of any sort! GPL software can be used by anyone just so long as they stick to the agreement with which they accepted the software.</p>\n<div align=\"center\"><img src=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-content/uploads/2007/11/sillystupidtypo.jpg\" alt=\"Silly Stupid Typo\" /></div>\n<p>As expected, <a href=\"http://palestinesolidarityproject.wordpress.com/\">palestinesolidarityproject.wordpress.com</a> points at an old blog of theirs as they have now moved to their own server at <a href=\"http://palestinesolidarityproject.org/\">palestinesolidarityproject.org</a>.</p>\n<p>Glossing over the .org mistake for a minute, why do people still put the &#8220;www.&#8221; in front of long-winded urls? It gets stripped by WordPress.com anyway. Why not put &#8220;http://&#8221; there instead? Makes more sense to me. Three cheers for the <a href=\"http://no-www.org/\">no-www</a> movement!</p>\n<p>So, have you seen any glaring typos on posters, fliers, stickers or blogs that made you look twice? Today&#8217;s <a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2007/11/21/donnchas-thursday-links-2007-11-21/\">link post</a> doesn&#8217;t count. I did that on purpose to make a point. Sure. <img src=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" /></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/?voyeur=1\" /></p><p><strong>Related Posts</strong><ul><li><a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2004/01/26/vodafoneie-doesnt-like-mozilla-firebird/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Vodafone.ie doesn&#8217;t like Mozilla Firebird\">Vodafone.ie doesn&#8217;t like Mozilla Firebird</a></li><li><a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2005/08/17/whats-this-wordpresscom-thing-anyway/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: What&#8217;s this WordPress.com thing anyway?\">What&#8217;s this WordPress.com thing anyway?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://ocaoimh.ie/2007/12/09/put-wordpress-on-the-map/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Put WordPress on the map\">Put WordPress on the map</a></li></ul></p>\";}i:46;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"Weblog Tools Collection: Visiting China\";s:4:\"guid\";s:68:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/11/21/visiting-china/\";s:4:\"link\";s:68:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/11/21/visiting-china/\";s:11:\"description\";s:704:\"<p>I will be traveling in China through the earlier part of December. This is a great opportunity for me to meet some of my Chinese readers, fellow bloggers and WordPress aficionados. If you are interested in meeting, are knowledgeable about the area or could provide some tips, please leave a comment or contact me directly. As the itinerary stands, the following times are open for me.</p>\n<p>Beijing: December 2nd, Evening</p>\n<p>Qinhuangdao: December 3rd and 4th, Evening</p>\n<p>Shanghai: December 6th and 9th, Evening</p>\n<p>Hangzhou: December 7th, Evening</p>\n<p>Judging from my reader statistics, I have quite a few readers in China. If you are reading this blog from China, where do you live?</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 21 Nov 2007 11:00:04 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:10:\"Mark Ghosh\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:704:\"<p>I will be traveling in China through the earlier part of December. This is a great opportunity for me to meet some of my Chinese readers, fellow bloggers and WordPress aficionados. If you are interested in meeting, are knowledgeable about the area or could provide some tips, please leave a comment or contact me directly. As the itinerary stands, the following times are open for me.</p>\n<p>Beijing: December 2nd, Evening</p>\n<p>Qinhuangdao: December 3rd and 4th, Evening</p>\n<p>Shanghai: December 6th and 9th, Evening</p>\n<p>Hangzhou: December 7th, Evening</p>\n<p>Judging from my reader statistics, I have quite a few readers in China. If you are reading this blog from China, where do you live?</p>\";}i:47;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:58:\"Weblog Tools Collection: Lijit: Search Stats for your Blog\";s:4:\"guid\";s:86:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/11/20/lijit-search-stats-for-your-blog/\";s:4:\"link\";s:86:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/11/20/lijit-search-stats-for-your-blog/\";s:11:\"description\";s:1182:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.lijit.com/\">Lijit</a> is a search tool/widget that you easily install on your blog. It lets you provide a comprehensive search of almost everything that you want, including integration with popular social networking tools such as Facebook. Lijit creates custom Google searches with your search items and then, I assume, puts up their own Google Ads in the searches. I <a href=\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/06/08/how-important-is-search/\">happen to think search statistics are very important for a blogger</a> to understand user trends, likes and dislikes. I noticed Lijit for the first time while reading about <a href=\"http://avc.blogs.com/a_vc/2007/11/kindling-this-b.html\">Kindling on A VC</a> and the name Lijit reminded me of <a href=\"http://www.lijjat.com/\">Lijjat</a> (which is a snack from India). I did setup an account to test out the services and you can see it at work on the sidebar of this blog. The popular search cloud and pretty cool set of stats are the killer set of features I was looking for. Give it a whirl on the sidebar.</p>\n<p>If you have tried <a href=\"http://www.lijit.com/\">Lijit</a>, what are your thoughts?</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Nov 2007 21:15:04 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:10:\"Mark Ghosh\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:1182:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.lijit.com/\">Lijit</a> is a search tool/widget that you easily install on your blog. It lets you provide a comprehensive search of almost everything that you want, including integration with popular social networking tools such as Facebook. Lijit creates custom Google searches with your search items and then, I assume, puts up their own Google Ads in the searches. I <a href=\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/06/08/how-important-is-search/\">happen to think search statistics are very important for a blogger</a> to understand user trends, likes and dislikes. I noticed Lijit for the first time while reading about <a href=\"http://avc.blogs.com/a_vc/2007/11/kindling-this-b.html\">Kindling on A VC</a> and the name Lijit reminded me of <a href=\"http://www.lijjat.com/\">Lijjat</a> (which is a snack from India). I did setup an account to test out the services and you can see it at work on the sidebar of this blog. The popular search cloud and pretty cool set of stats are the killer set of features I was looking for. Give it a whirl on the sidebar.</p>\n<p>If you have tried <a href=\"http://www.lijit.com/\">Lijit</a>, what are your thoughts?</p>\";}i:48;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:60:\"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 11/20\";s:4:\"guid\";s:88:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/11/20/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-1120/\";s:4:\"link\";s:88:\"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2007/11/20/wordpress-plugin-releases-for-1120/\";s:11:\"description\";s:1155:\"<p><a href=\"http://www.artonesia.org/2007/11/15/adbrite-widgets/\">Adbrite Widgets</a> shows ads from adbrite.com as widgets.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/goodreadsplugin/\">GoodReads</a> allows a user to display the RSS feed of one of their Goodreads shelves on their WordPress weblog.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pokerup.de/wordpress-plugin-playing-cards-generator\">WordPress Playing Cards Generator</a> lets you display various combinations of playing cards in card games like canasta, thirty-one, pinochle or poker.  (<a href=\"http://wp-plugins.net/plugin/playing-cards-generator/#plugin_2977\">English download.</a>)</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.geekyramblings.org/plugins/wp-tags-to-technorati\">WP Tags to Technorati</a> turns your WordPress tags into Technorati tags.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dealsway.net/2007/11/05/wp-user-manager/\">WP User Manager</a> aims at improving the Wordpress User Management so that Wordpress can be used beyond a blog and something like a CMS.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dealsway.net/2007/09/04/wp-user-moderation/\">WP User Moderation</a> helps to moderate and approve the Wordpress User Account generation.</p>\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Nov